defs.name: scalar
defs.docs:
This module provides an implementation of the BLS12-381 scalar field $\mathbb{F}_q$
 where `q = 0x73eda753299d7d483339d80809a1d80553bda402fffe5bfeffffffff00000001`

defs.name: Scalar
defs.docs:
Represents an element of the scalar field $\mathbb{F}_q$ of the BLS12-381 elliptic
 curve construction.

defs.name: MODULUS
defs.docs:
Constant representing the modulus
 q = 0x73eda753299d7d483339d80809a1d80553bda402fffe5bfeffffffff00000001

defs.name: R
defs.docs: R = 2^256 mod q

defs.name: ROOT_OF_UNITY
defs.docs:
GENERATOR^t where t * 2^s + 1 = q
 with t odd. In other words, this
 is a 2^s root of unity.

defs.name: G1Affine
defs.docs:
This is an element of $\mathbb{G}_1$ represented in the affine coordinate space.
 It is ideal to keep elements in this representation to reduce memory usage and
 improve performance through the use of mixed curve model arithmetic.

defs.name: identity
defs.docs: Returns the identity of the group: the point at infinity.

defs.name: generator
defs.docs:
Returns a fixed generator of the group. See [`notes::design`](notes/design/index.html#fixed-generators)
 for how this generator is chosen.

defs.name: to_compressed
defs.docs:
Serializes this element into compressed form. See [`notes::serialization`](crate::notes::serialization)
 for details about how group elements are serialized.

defs.name: to_uncompressed
defs.docs:

 for details about how group elements are serialized.

defs.name: from_uncompressed
defs.docs:
Attempts to deserialize an uncompressed element. See [`notes::serialization`](crate::notes::serialization)
 for details about how group elements are serialized.

defs.name: from_uncompressed_unchecked
defs.docs:
Attempts to deserialize an uncompressed element, not checking if the
 element is on the curve and not checking if it is in the correct subgroup.
 **This is dangerous to call unless you trust the bytes you are reading; otherwise,
 API invariants may be broken.** Please consider using `from_uncompressed()` instead.

defs.name: is_torsion_free
defs.docs:

 exists within the $q$-order subgroup $\mathbb{G}_1$. This should always return true
 unless an "unchecked" API was used.

defs.name: MillerLoopResult
defs.docs:
Represents results of a Miller loop, one of the most expensive portions
 of the pairing function. `MillerLoopResult`s cannot be compared with each
 other until `.final_exponentiation()` is called, which is also expensive.

defs.name: final_exponentiation
defs.docs:
This performs a "final exponentiation" routine to convert the result
 of a Miller loop into an element of `Gt` so that it can be compared
 with other elements of `Gt`.

defs.name: Gt
defs.docs:
This is an element of $\mathbb{G}_T$, the target group of the pairing function. As with
 $\mathbb{G}_1$ and $\mathbb{G}_2$ this group has order $q$.

defs.name: identity
defs.docs: Returns the group identity, which is $1$.

defs.docs: Doubles this group element.
